issue.body:
Hi, I have the following issue.

Setup:
```php
// request.php - Yii2 request component setup

return [
    'request' => [
        'class' => 'app\components\web\Request',
        ...
```

```php
// singletons.php - singleton classes

return [
    app\components\web\Request::class => [],
    ...
```

Why I have this? Well because I wanted to be able to take advantage of the dependency injection like in Yii3 right now, so I can:
```php
    public function actionSomething(
        \app\components\web\Request $request)
```

but I can also `Yii::$app->request` in the places where I already have that.
In both cases I get the same single instance of the Request with the data correctly set.

My problem in tests is that if I need to send 2 requests, then with the `CLEAN_FORCE_RECREATE` or `CLEAN_RECREATE` mode, this line
```php
$app->set('request', $app->getComponents()['request'])
```
does not actually reset the request object, because it uses the same `Request` class instance which is a singleton in the container.

On the other mode, `CLEAN_CLEAR` the problem for me is that `$request->getHeaders()->removeAll();` does not actually set `$request->_headers` back to null, so the `getHeaders` method from the `yii\web\Request` class does not correctly repopulate.

So basically, because there no way for me to modify the `CLEAN_CLEAR` functionality, because `_headers` is private, what I did is I still use the `CLEAN_RECREATE` mode but with the following code:
```php
// /Lib/Connector/Yii2.php

protected function resetRequest(Application $app) {
       ...
       ...
        if ($this->requestCleanMethod === self::CLEAN_RECREATE) {
            $container = \Yii::$container;
            $request = $app->getComponents()['request'];
            $requestDefinition = $container->getDefinitions()[$request['class']] ?? null;
            // Reset the singleton instance on the container to make sure the request instance will be recreated
            if ($container->hasSingleton($request['class'], true) && $requestDefinition !== null) {
                $container->setSingleton($request['class'], $requestDefinition);
            }
        }
```

So my question is, what do you think about this? Should this be something handled in the code for other people as well, should this be a merge request? Should we also find a way to fix the "headers" reset?
Thanks.
